SECTION 1: OVERVIEW
================================================================================

This policy establishes guidelines for business travel and expense 
reimbursement for all Nexus Cloud Solutions employees. Compliance with 
this policy is mandatory for expense reimbursement.

================================================================================
SECTION 2: AIRFARE
================================================================================

2.1 Booking Requirements
- Book through approved travel portal (Concur) when possible
- Economy class required for flights under 6 hours
- Economy Plus/Premium Economy permitted for flights 4+ hours
- Business class requires VP approval for flights over 8 hours

2.2 Advance Booking
- Book at least 14 days in advance when possible
- Last-minute bookings (< 7 days) require manager justification

================================================================================
SECTION 3: LODGING
================================================================================

3.1 Nightly Rate Limits (Including Taxes & Fees)

Tier 1 Cities (NYC, SF, LA, Chicago, Boston, Seattle, DC):
  - Standard: $350/night
  - Conference hotels: $450/night (with documentation)

Tier 2 Cities (Las Vegas, Denver, Austin, Miami, etc.):
  - Standard: $275/night
  - Conference hotels: $400/night (with documentation)

Tier 3 Cities (All other domestic):
  - Standard: $200/night

International: Refer to GSA per diem rates

3.2 Exceptions
- Conference venue hotels may exceed limits with prior approval
- Document conference rate vs. standard rate for justification

================================================================================
SECTION 4: MEALS & PER DIEM
================================================================================

4.1 Daily Meal Allowances (Domestic)

                    Breakfast    Lunch    Dinner    TOTAL
Tier 1 Cities:        $20        $25       $50       $95
Tier 2 Cities:        $18        $22       $45       $85
Tier 3 Cities:        $15        $20       $40       $75

Las Vegas specifically: $85/day total

4.2 Business Meals with Clients/Partners
- Pre-approval required for meals exceeding $75/person
- Maximum: $150/person for business dinners
- Document: Names, titles, companies, business purpose
- Alcohol: NOT REIMBURSABLE (see Section 8)

4.3 Solo Dining Limits
- Breakfast: $25 maximum
- Lunch: $30 maximum  
- Dinner: $75 maximum (Tier 1/2 cities)
- Dinner: $50 maximum (Tier 3 cities)

================================================================================
SECTION 5: GROUND TRANSPORTATION
================================================================================

5.1 Daily Limits
- Taxi/Rideshare: $75/day maximum
- Rental car: Economy class, $65/day maximum (excluding fuel)

5.2 Airport Transportation
- Rideshare/taxi to/from airport: Actual cost reimbursed
- Parking at airport: Long-term lot preferred, max $25/day

5.3 Conference Transportation
- Shuttle services preferred when available
- Rideshare permitted when shuttles unavailable or impractical

================================================================================
SECTION 6: CONFERENCE & REGISTRATION FEES
================================================================================

6.1 Approval Requirements
- Registration > $500: Manager approval required
- Registration > $2,000: VP approval required

6.2 Payment Method
- Conference registration should be paid via company PO when possible
- If paid on corporate card, attach PO or pre-approval documentation

================================================================================
SECTION 7: RECEIPT REQUIREMENTS
================================================================================

7.1 Receipt Thresholds
- Expenses $25 and under: Receipt preferred but not required
- Expenses over $25: Itemized receipt REQUIRED
- Expenses over $75: Itemized receipt + business justification

7.2 Missing Receipts
- Form HR-127 (Missing Receipt Affidavit) required
- Manager signature required
- Credit card statement must be attached
- Maximum 2 missing receipt claims per trip

7.3 Unreadable/Damaged Receipts
- Note the issue in expense report
- Attach credit card statement as backup
- Form HR-127 may be required at approver discretion

================================================================================
SECTION 8: NON-REIMBURSABLE EXPENSES
================================================================================

The following are NOT eligible for reimbursement:

- Alcoholic beverages (all circumstances)
- Personal entertainment (movies, shows, gambling)
- Personal phone calls exceeding $10
- Spouse/companion travel expenses
- Pet care/boarding
- Personal grooming (haircuts, spa services)
- Gym fees
- Laundry (trips under 5 days)
- Upgrades not authorized in advance
- Traffic/parking violations
- Lost or stolen items
- Expenses paid by another party

================================================================================
SECTION 9: EXPENSE REPORT SUBMISSION
================================================================================

9.1 Deadlines
- Submit within 30 calendar days of trip completion
- Late submissions (31-60 days): Require manager approval
- Submissions > 60 days: Require VP approval, subject to denial

9.2 Required Documentation
- Itemized receipts for all expenses > $25
- Business purpose for each expense category
- Attendee list for all business meals
- Conference agenda for registration fees
- Approval documentation for any exceptions

9.3 Approval Workflow
- < $1,000: Direct manager approval
- $1,000 - $5,000: Manager + Finance review
- > $5,000: Manager + Finance + VP approval

================================================================================
SECTION 10: POLICY VIOLATIONS
================================================================================

10.1 Consequences
- First violation: Written warning, required policy training
- Second violation: Expense privileges suspended (30 days)
- Third violation: Disciplinary action up to termination

10.2 Fraud
- Intentional misrepresentation is grounds for immediate termination
- Company reserves right to pursue legal action

